Figs. 16–18
) nearly 1.3 times wider than long, without impressions, sides weakly rounded and narrowly explanated. Lateral sides nearly straight and parallel to each other at basal two thirds, converging abruptly at apical one third. Anterolateral callosity well developed, varying in shape. Posterolateral callosity not protruding. Anterolateral callosity as long as or slightly less

